WEBVTT

00:01.435 --> 00:03.569
Narrator: TODAY ON
"IMPOSSIBLE ENGINEERING,"

00:03.571 --> 00:06.305
THE WORLD'S LARGEST WARSHIP.

00:06.307 --> 00:08.340
THE AIRCRAFT CARRIER
IS A MOVING CITY

00:08.342 --> 00:10.376
WITH ALL OF THE CAPABILITIES
OF ANY AIRFIELD,

00:10.378 --> 00:12.177
AND IT CAN BE MOVED
ANYWHERE IN THE WORLD.

00:12.179 --> 00:16.248
Narrator: 4-1/2 ACRES OF
CUTTING-EDGE MILITARY MUSCLE...

00:16.250 --> 00:18.417
THE FORD CLASS HAS
TAKEN A 40-YEAR LEAP

00:18.419 --> 00:21.787
IN THE DEVELOPMENT OF
AIRCRAFT CARRIER TECHNOLOGIES.

00:21.789 --> 00:25.424
Narrator: ...AND THE PIONEERING
HISTORIC INNOVATIONS...

00:25.426 --> 00:27.292
MAN, I LOVE THE SMELL
OF JET FUEL IN THE MORNING.

00:27.294 --> 00:28.427
YOU KNOW WHAT I MEAN?

00:28.429 --> 00:29.928
LET'S GO AHEAD
AND LAUNCH THE SECOND.

00:29.930 --> 00:32.264
AND YOU CAN SEE THAT
THOSE TWO FLIGHT PATHS

00:32.266 --> 00:34.299
ARE NATURALLY DE-CONFLICTED.

00:34.301 --> 00:36.201
Narrator:
...THAT MADE THE IMPOSSIBLE

00:36.203 --> 00:38.370
POSSIBLE.

00:38.372 --> 00:41.373
